GIT
- multiple ppl can work on a same project at the same time (fast deployment)
-Revert to the older version if the new version as some bug of fails


GIT is a Technology
GIT-HUB is a platform



	TYPES
LOCAL --- within ones Sys
CENTRALIZED --- Collab , but cant be Backup when crashed
DISTRIBUTED --- Collab ,Can be Backup when crashed    -- e.g.. Bitbucket ,Git-Hub



git config --global user.name "Shiva Parasuram R"  // name
git config --global user.email "shivaparasuramr@gmail.com  //email
git config --global --list                   //Check the name and email (Return Info)

HTTP ask login all the time
SSH -one time login -- read automatically login credentials


MANIPULATE REPOSATORY
commad prompt
git bash



CD //change location

git init // create MT repository
commit  //save

git add filename.extension          // to add single file
git add .                          //to add all the file
git commit                        // to save
git commit -m"first message"     //with message


two Branches -
main  branch
Master branch


git branch -M main
can create new branch also

know who did the changes
git log  //know history


git remote remove origin -- if duplicate exist

	HTTP
ask for login all the time



    PUSH (only update in existing file)

git add GIT
git commit -m "Update"
git push -u origin main


    SSH
Generate a Special key
Don't ask login all the time
create the key always outside the project

we need key before v go to

    COMMANDS
mkdir JFSJD   //create new project
cd JFSJD  // go inside the project
ls  //check any files are there
pwd // current location
echo "hello developers" >> abc.txt //echo to write in abc file
cat abc.txt //read directly
cd //come out of project
ls -a //show all the file created like ssh file(inside tht v have .pub file that is the ssh key use cat id to see)

git remote -v//1.local to remote (push)
             //2.remote to local (fetch)

touch a.txt //create mt file
echo "HELLO" >> filName.ex   // insert with data long term
echo "Hii" > filName.ex   // insert with data short term
cp a.text c.txt    //copy from one file to other
mv b.txt a.txt    //move b to a
rm c.txt      //remove c
ls -a // view all files
rm -r Folder name   // delete the folder


    IN COMMAND PROMPT
type to read
copy a.txt           //copy
dir              // to see files
/q /s Java         //to delete folder with files
del Java       // delete single file
type nul>a.txt   //create null file
